.TH "Document.hasFocus" "JS" "July 26, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Document.hasFocus \- Document: hasFocus() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]hasFocus()\f[B]\f[R] method of the \f[CR]Document\f[R]
interface returns a boolean value indicating whether the document or any
element inside the document has focus.
This method can be used to determine whether the active element in a
document has focus.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] When viewing a document, an element with focus is always
the active element in the document, but an active element does not
necessarily have focus.
For example, an active element within a popup window that is not the
foreground doesn\[cq]t have focus.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
hasFocus()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
\f[CR]false\f[R] if the active element in the document has no focus;
\f[CR]true\f[R] if the active element in the document has focus.
.SH EXAMPLES
The following example checks whether the document has focus or not.
A function called \f[CR]checkPageFocus()\f[R] updates a paragraph
element depending on the result of \f[CR]document.hasFocus()\f[R].
Opening a new window will cause the document to lose focus and switching
back to the original window will cause the document to regain focus.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]p\f[R] id=\[dq]log\[dq]>Focus check results are shown here.</\f[B]p\f[R]>
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\[dq]newWindow\[dq]>Open new window</\f[B]button\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] body = document.querySelector(\[dq]body\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] log = document.getElementById(\[dq]log\[dq]);

\f[B]function\f[R] checkDocumentFocus() {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (document.hasFocus()) {
    log.textContent = \[dq]This document has focus.\[dq];
    body.style.background = \[dq]white\[dq];
  } \f[B]else\f[R] {
    log.textContent = \[dq]This document does not have focus.\[dq];
    body.style.background = \[dq]gray\[dq];
  }
}

\f[B]function\f[R] openWindow() {
  window.open(
    \[dq]https://developer.mozilla.org/\[dq],
    \[dq]MDN\[dq],
    \[dq]width=640,height=320,left=150,top=150\[dq],
  );
}

document.getElementById(\[dq]newWindow\[dq]).addEventListener(\[dq]click\[dq], openWindow);
setInterval(checkDocumentFocus, 300);
.EE
